  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-03 stale-data variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. The primary experimental benchmark dataset (FDA pump PIV/hemolysis measurements) carries a dataVintage of 2025-11-03, predating the model revision of 2025-11-24 by three weeks. The revision corrected the turbulent viscosity limiter coefficient and updated the Giersiepen–Wurzinger hemolysis exponents; the assessment narrative characterises this change as 'not material to the benchmark dataset relevance' without formal re-validation against the updated model build. Decision: Accepted.",
